A vintage 1950s style illustration of a mechanical postal sorting machine gone haywire, with identical envelopes caught in an endless loop, being ejected from one slot only to be sucked back into another intake chute. The machine is ornate brass and copper with spinning gears and pneumatic tubes, sitting in a retro mail room with wood-paneled walls. Piles of rejected envelopes accumulate beneath the machine while a single envelope desperately tries to reach a small "REPORT" inbox that keeps getting blocked by the machine's own mechanical arms. The color palette features muted teals, warm oranges, and sepia tones typical of mid-century advertising illustrations.
